(10, 1, 0, 'GRDJEV01I010010', 0, NULL, 'LOAD SHARING OF TRANSFORMERS WITH TEMPERATURE MONITORING – A TECHNICAL RESEARCH', 'load sharing of transformers', 1, 8, '', 'transformer, temperature monitoring', '            Distribution transformers are an important part of power system which distributes power to the low-voltage users directly, and its operation condition However, there is important for the entire distribution network operation. Life is significantly reduced if they are subjected to overloading and over temperature resulting in unexpected failures and loss of supply to a large number of customers thus effecting system reliability. Protection against fault in power systems is very essential and virtual for its reliable performance. Thus to protect the transformers from overloads and over temperature, the concept of load sharing has been proposed, wherein, automatic load sharing occurs whenever the rated conditions are exceeded. ', '', 'Prof. Nilkanth A Patel ', 'ipcowala institute of engineering and technology, dharamaj', 'nilkanth.eee@gmail.com', '9898796964', 'ipcowala institute of engineering and technology', 'amrapali township dharamaj', 'anand', '388430', 'gujarat', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I01/0010/1450844366_electrical-paper.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Partial Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Partial Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Partial Agree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Disagree","comment":"This article is not acceptable,\\r\\nThis work is already published and very high plagiarism is found.\\r\\nSo this article should be reject."}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 3, 'GRDJE/V01/I01/0010/', '1', 0, 0, 0, '2015-12-23 09:49:28', 0, '2015-12-28 11:03:58', 1, 1),
(11, 1, 0, 'GRDJEV01I010011', 0, NULL, 'Reducing Human Effort: Web Data Mining, Learning a New Characteristics from Big Data', 'Web Data Mining', 1, 4, '', 'Big Data, DOM, Extraction Pattern, Wrapper Learning & Adaption.', 'This paper presents a Reducing Human Effort: Web Data Mining, Learning a New Characteristics from Big data, reducing human effort in extracting precise information from undetected Web sites. Our approach aims at automatically adapting the information extraction knowledge previously learned from a source Web site to a new undetected site, at the same time, discovering previously undetected attributes. There is a two kinds of text related evidences from the source Web site are considered. The first kind of evidences is obtained from the extraction pattern contained in the previously learned wrapper. The second kind of evidences is derived from the previously extracted or collected items. A generative model for the generation of the web site independent content information and the site dependent layout format of the text fragments related to attribute values contained in a Web page is designed to connect the insecurity involved. We have conducted extensive experiments from more than 50 real world Web sites in more than five different domains to demonstrate the effectiveness of our context.', '', 'Mr.M.Srinivasan.', 'Priyadarshini Engineering College, Vaniyambadi, Vellore, India', 'srinivasanpecit@gmail.com', '9943760179', 'Priyadarshini Engineering College, ', 'Vaniyambadi,', 'Vellore, India', '635751', 'Tamilnadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I01/0011/1450854173_M.Srinivasan-Reducing-Human-Effort.doc', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"A