(12, 1, 0, 'GRDJEV01I010012', 0, NULL, 'Hydro Petrol Engine - A Technical Review', 'hydro petrol engine', 2, 6, '', 'hydrogen, petrol, four stroke engine', 'Over the years, global energy demand has been enormously increased as a result of industrial development and population growth. Supply of energy is far less than the actual demand which contributes to unstable oil price. Other fossil fuel is the major contributor of harmful aspects of human activity and biophysical environment issue. This projects is attempts to investigate performance of hydro-petrol engine system as an alternative to reduce dependencies to fossil fuel; emitting less harmful gaseous to the environment. For this system, oxygen or hydrogen (H2 or O2) gas was produced through electrolysis method before channeled into air intake manifold of a typical 4 stroke petrol engine. The research measured petrol consumption as well as the by-product gaseous. It was found that the fuel consumption reduced to 22% while the CO2 and HC gases reduced in this engine system. Feasibility of the concluded research data will become a pathway for more comprehensive and depth study on hydro-petrol engine.', '', 'Bhavin Atulbhai Gajjar', 'ipcowala institute of engineering and technology, dharamaj', 'bhavingajjar13b@yahoo.com', '9879585631', 'ipcowala institute of engineering and technology', 'amrapali township dharamaj', 'anand', '388430', 'gujarat', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I01/0012/1451302453_finalmoulik-review-paper.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the e