(19, 2, 0, 'GRDJEV01I020003', 4, NULL, 'Experimental Studies on Concrete with Bentonite as Mineral Admixture', 'concrete technology', 1, 10, '', 'Bentonite clay, flexural strength, compressive strength, split tensile strength ', 'The present investigation deals with effect of bentonite clay on concrete. The concrete was produced by partial replacement of OPC with mineral admixture bentonite clay in percentages of 0%, 5%, 10%, 15% and 20%. The M20 grade of concrete was designed. The compressive strength, split tensile strength and flexural strength were found for the specimens. The present investigation is to study the effect of bentonite clay on concrete. The results indicate that the concrete 5% replacement shows better performance when compared to other samples. The compressive strength, split tensile strength and flexural strength at 5% bentonite clay replacement and it was less for the remaining samples.', '', 'M.Chandrakanth', 'SIR C R REDDY COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING', 'ksrao.ce@gmail.com', '9966336955', 'SIR C R REDDY COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING', 'DEPARTMENT OF CIVIL ENGINEERING', 'Eluru', '534007', 'ANDHRA PRADESH', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I02/0003/1452706631_GRDJEV01I020003.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Fully Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Fully Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Fully Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Fully Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Agree","comment":"I have no objec