(20, 2, 0, 'GRDJEV01I020004', 0, NULL, 'Protonation equilibria of L-Glutamic acid and L-Histidine in low dielectric media', 'Chemical Speciation ', 1, 13, 'Chemical Science', 'Protonation equilibria, DMSO, Glutamic acid, Histidine, MINIQUAD75', 'Effect of DMSO on the protonation equilibria of L-Glutamic acid and L-Histidine  have been studied in varying concentrations (0-60% v/v) of DMSO–water mixtures maintaining an ionic strength of 0.16 mol/l at 303 K using pH metric method. The protonation constants have been calculated with the computer program MINIQUAD75 and the best fit models are arrived at based on statistical grounds employing crystallographic R factor, χ2, skewness and kurtosis. The variation of protonation constants with dielectric constant of the medium is attributed to the electrostatic and non-electrostatic forces. The effect of errors on the protonation constants has also been presented.', '', 'Prof. G. Nageswara Rao', 'Department of Inorganic Chemistry, School of Chemistry, Andhra University, Vishakapatnam.', 'gollapallinr@yahoo.com', '9440306372', 'Department of Inorganic Chemistry', 'School of Chemistry', 'Andhra University, Vishakapatnam', '530003', 'Andhra pradesh', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I02/0004/1453080882_Raju-Paper.doc', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Agree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journa