(28, 3, 0, 'GRDJEV01I030002', 21, NULL, 'DESIGN AND FABRICATION OF HYDRAULIC BEARING PULLERS', 'Mechanical', 1, 6, '', 'Aluminium alloy based composite, Coconut Shell Ash, Silicon Carbide, Stir Casting, Hardness and Wear', ' Is mainly concentrating on this difficulty, and hence a suitable device is designed, such that the bearing can be removed from the bearing shaft with the application of hydraulic force. The fabrication part of it is considered for its simplicity and economy, such that this can be accommodated as one of the essential tools in automobile garages. Here, we go in for a bearing puller to remove the bearings usually. But often it is felt tedious to wear in bearings and shafts, even by using the mechanical puller. This makes it difficult work to be done by the mechanics in the workshops, while removing the bearings. Hence we have come with an idea of hydraulic bearing puller. Fabrication of this is our concentrated theme. In order to reduce the above mentioned wear in the bearing, it is provided with hydraulic sources to operate it very easily. This device is compact, easy to operate and anyone can operate it, even old aged. Here we employ hydraulic bottle jack as main component which is used to pull the bearing from the shaft. And to hold the work piece, arm arrangement is used.', '', 'L.Sanjitkumaran', 'Sathyabama University, Chennai', 'ragulragul91@gmail.com', '7405407107', 'Sathyabama University, Chennai', 'Rajiv Gandhi Road, Jeppiaar Nagar,', 'Solinganallur', '600119', 'Tamilnadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I03/0002/1454474776_Sanjit-Kumaran.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Disagree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Disagree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe wit