(30, 3, 0, 'GRDJEV01I030005', 0, NULL, 'Optimum machine selection for Flexible Manufacturing System', 'Optimization', 1, 6, '', 'FMS, CNC, MCDM, AHP, TOPSIS', 'Selection of the optimum CNC among a pool of alternatives is a multi-criteria decision making (MCDM) problem. In this paper, an evaluation model based on the fuzzy analytic hierarchy process (AHP) and another fuzzy MCDM technique, namely fuzzy technique for order performance by similarity to ideal solution (TOPSIS) is used in CNC selection under fuzzy environment where the uncertainty is taken into account with linguistic variables parameterized by fuzzy numbers. The fuzzy AHP is applied to form the structure of the CNC selection problem and to determine weights of the evaluation criteria, and fuzzy TOPSIS method is used to acquire final ranking. ', '', 'Dinesh R', 'PPG Institute of Technology, Coimbatore, India.', 'dinshragubathi@gmail.com', '9786417277', '3/294, Kuruthukuli village', 'Kuruthukuli post', 'Ooty', '643004', 'Tamil Nadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I03/0005/1454667878_Optimum-CNC-machine-selection-for-Flexible-Manufacturing-System.docx', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 1, 'GRDJE/V01/I03/0005/', '1', 0, 0, 0, '2016-02-05 15:54:38', 0, '2016-03-11 10:06:57', 1, 1),
