(32, 3, 0, 'GRDJEV01I030007', 28, NULL, 'UNCONVENTIONAL MODELING AND STRESS ANALYSIS OF FEMUR BONE UNDER DIFFERENT BOUNDARY CONDITION', 'Electronics & Communication ', 1, 7, '', 'ANSYS; Finite Element Analysis; Femur bone; Biomechanics', 'Femur is leg bone of the human body undergoing the more deformations. Being longest and the heaviest size, failure of a femur neck is the most common among them bone failures in human especially of woman. Orthopedic implantation has done by case of failure. Before implantation method is necessary to be analyzing their perfectness in the case of its material property, load resistance, size, shape, surface treatment chances of failure. Since each femur carries 1/2 the body weight, analysis is done for as 25kg, 50kg, 100kg, 200kg load includes the case of patients carrying the certain weight. From these analysis methods is found their load has been no effects on failure of implantation, since these values of stresses and deformations is very low. Thus failure of implantations is maximum by wearing this corrosion, all due to improper material selection of implant.\r\nFinally the success of implantations depends on implant material and sizes, implantation method and its handling by the patient.\r\n', '', 'M.Ragulkumar', 'Shree Sathyam College of Engineering and Technology, Sankari', 'rksjournal@gmail.com', '9597825169', 'Shree Sathyam College of Engineering and Technology, Sankari', 'Pallipalayam - Sankari Rd,', 'Sankari', '637301', 'Tamilnadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I03/0007/1454951346_DIP.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Fully Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Agree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Fully Agree","comment":"Review Report:\\r\\n\\r\\nIntroduction:\\r\\n\\r\\nThis paper is about to review on bone fracture Properties using Simulation Techniques. Simulation used here is ANSYS.\\r\\n\\r\\nTheme Review:\\r\\n\\r\\nTheme chosen is Femur bone, which is longest bone from hip to Knee. The Author discussed about the fracture Properties of Femur bone. But I cannot come to a conclusion why femur bone alone is chosen, since there are other 2 bones in our Leg namely tibia and Fibula.\\r\\nIf that was also taken it would be Perfect. Since we might have got different Simulation results for Analysis. However I appreciate the theme chosen by Author.\\r\\n\\r\\nTechnical Review:\\r\\n\\r\\nAuthor used PMOS,NMOS concepts for analyzing the Properties of Fractured Bones. However the Simulation directly fetches the results without explaining the various stages of Operation in the Transistors. The information in Cut Off, Triode and Saturation regions are Missing in Analysis. That comparison is required to Come to the Bone breakage Properties at various Levels.\\r\\n\\r\\nAppreciate the Finite element Analysis with Simulation Outputs which shows the Properties of femur Bones.\\r\\n\\r\\nBacklogs by author:\\r\\n\\r\\nIf Computational Stress Analysis is taken into Picture then it would be more Perfect .But unfortunately author has not taken that for Simulation Purposes.\\r\\n\\r\\nImportant Properties covered  by author:\\r\\n\\r\\nDeformation,Von-Mises Stress and Strain Equivalent Condition are the Properties covered which is much appreciable.\\r\\n\\r\\nConclusion:\\r\\n\\r\\nI Recommend this paper to be published in E-Journal .\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n"}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 5, 'GRDJE/V01/I03/0007/', '1', 0, 0, 0, '2016-02-08 22:39:07', 0, '2016-02-11 22:46:06', 1, 0),
(33, 3, 0, 'GRDJEV01I030008', 33, NULL, ' A Study of Properties,Preperation and Testing of  Magneto- Rheological (MR) Fluid ', 'Mechanical Engineering', 1, 6, '', 'Keywords: Magneto Rheological (MR) fluid, Magneto         Rheological (MR) Damper, Smart Materials, Controllable fluids', 'Abstract-Magneto rheological (MR) fluids have been investigated to be of much importance due to their magneto rheological dependant properties. Magneto Rheological is a branch of rheology that deals with the flow and deformation of the materials under an applied magnetic field. These types of materials change their rheological properties under the application of magnetic field applied and turn from liquid to solid in just few seconds. MR fluid is the colloidal suspension of micron sized, polarizable magnetic particles (iron metal particle) in the magnetically neutral carrier fluid (low viscosity paraffin oil / silicon oil) whose viscosity can be varied from liquid to semisolid with the help of magnetic field. \r\n                Magneto rheological (MR) fluid technology has been proven for many industrial applications like shock absorbers, actuators, seat dampers, etc.. This paper presents basic properties, preparation, testing and implementation of MR fluid in conventional damper.\r\n', '', 'Abhijeet Vijay Sonawane', 'Amrutvahini  College of Engg. Sangamner Pune, India.', 'abhisonawane009@gmail.com', '8605242045', 'PURANDARE WADA (HOSTEL) SHANIWAR PETH PUNE 411030', 'SHANIWAR PETH', 'PUNE', '411030', 'MAHARASHTRA', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I03/0008/1455548978_PURANDAREfinal.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Fully Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity 