(58, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040076', 96, NULL, 'INCREMENTAL MAP REDUCE FRAMEWORK FOR EFFICIENT MINING EVOLVING IN BIG DATA ENVIRONMENT', 'Big data', 1, 4, '', 'Map reduce, Data mining, incremental process, Bipartite graph, computation, iteration', 'Keeping in mind the constant growth of data, we require more efficient ways to store and retrieve data. As the data mining techniques that are currently being used become ineffective, new methods or some modifications in the application of the existing techniques becomes a necessity. In this project, the data mining technique that is being used is incremental Map reduce. When the volume of data increases, the computation process becomes tedious. To avoid this problem and to increase the efficiency of data mining we can make use of incremental map reduce process. Wherein, the past output is used to find the key-value pair rather than working from the scratch every time using the BipartiteGraph. By iterating the MapReduce process we can handle dynamic changes in the data efficiently.', '', 'Lekha .L', 'Velammal Institute of Technology, Chennai, India', 'lekhalingeshwar.17@gmail.com', '9600053548', 'Velammal Institute of Technology, Chennai, India', 'Thiruvallur District, ', 'Chennai', '601204', 'Tamil Nadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0076/1458403691_Map-Reduce-1.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Fully Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Fully Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Fully Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Fully Agree","Method was describe in details":"Fully Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Fully Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Fully Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Fully Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Agree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Fully Agree","comment":"The main contribution of this research is to propose the incremental MapReduce framework with Bipartite Graph for improving data mining in big data. The proposed incremental MapReduce minimizes the number of re-computations. The most important point of the research is Bipartite Graph which is used to determine state changes in order to support reduce function to save computational operators. The idea and technique of Bipartite Graph is excellent. I have no special comments except that authors should remove the option \\"Allow Latin text in the middle of a word\\" in Word paragraph format in order to enhance the appearance. I agree to publish the article in GRD journals."}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 5, 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0076/', '1', 0, 0, 0, '2016-03-19 21:38:12', 0, '2016-03-24 22:51:45', 1, 0),
