(61, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040078', 35, NULL, 'RBI 3X-Fingerprint Based ATM Machine', 'Electronics and Tele-Communication', 1, 14, '', 'ATmega16 microcontroller, Finger print recognition, Liquid Crystal Display, DC motor', 'The main objective of this system is to develop a system that will increase the ATM security. However, despite the numerous advantages of ATM system, ATM fraud has recently become more widespread. In this paper, we provide an overview of the possible fraudulent activities that may be perpetrated against ATMs and investigates recommended approaches to prevent these types of frauds..Biometrics technology is rapidly progressing and offers attractive opportunities. In recent years, biometric authentication has grown in popularity as a means of personal identification in ATM authentication systems. An 8-bit ATmega16 microcontroller developed by Microchip Technology is used in the system. The necessary software is written in AVR studio programmer and the system is tested.', '', 'Bharti Patil', 'PVPIT, Bavdhan, Pune', 'bchandrekar007@gmail.com', '8600260201', 'S.N. 33/22, Near. Chandni Chowk,Opp. Athashree Project, ', 'Pirangut Road, Bavdhan, Pune, Maharashtra 411021', 'Pune', '411021', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0078/1458476451_New-RBI-3X-1.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Fully Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not ha