(76, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040083', 58, NULL, 'A Review paper Based on Memory BIST', 'electronics and telecommunication , VLSI', 2, 7, '', '— Built-in Self-Test, Random Access Memory, CUT circuit under test, TPG Test Pattern Generation, Response Analysis', 'today memory is an essential component, memory cells are arranged in a symmetrical manner each cell should work properly for the appropriate output. These cells are a symmetrical arrangement of capacitors when they are charged shows logic 1 for the Binary output, this access the value to show required address or data. Now, as the technology is shrinking challenges with testing of circuits, increasing exponentially, it is not that simple to test each and every component of the circuit. On the other hand, they have a number of faults which cause failure to detect the accurate data of the given address. Less area, more speed, and less power consumption are the main constraints of today’s technology. These constraints kept in mind in this proposed project to design such a BIST circuit, which will provide the efficient output.', '', 'Ritu Singh Thakur', 'Dr. C. V. Raman University, kota Bilaspur', 'ritusingh47873@gmail.com', '9039768772', 'Parijat Extension SMIG c 65 ', 'Gaurav path, near Pallav Bhavan', 'Bilaspur ', '495001', 'chhatisgarh', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0083/1458618192_paper-for-review-grd-journal.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Disagree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Disagree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Disagree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Disagree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Disagree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgemen