(77, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040084', 72, NULL, 'QR Code based Digitized Mark sheet System', 'Information Processing, Security', 1, 12, '', 'Keywords—— result; digitized mark-sheet; QR Code; encryption', 'Abstract—Now a days, the world is becoming digital and use of \r\n\r\ndigital data is growing. hence, it is very important to optimize \r\n\r\nthese data and secure or preserve them  in an eco-friendly \r\n\r\nmanner. In this paper, the auther presents a new method to \r\n\r\ndigitize the academic marksheets, and embed the digital data in \r\n\r\nthe marksheet itself in the form of encrypted QR Code, so that \r\n\r\nthese digital data can not be retrieved by unauthorized person. \r\n\r\nBy using this method , we can save a lot of digital space, which \r\n\r\nwill further necessary to save those digital academic records of \r\n\r\neach student. In our new marksheet system, the digital data, \r\n\r\nwhich is enclosed in the marksheet in form of encrypted QR \r\n\r\ncode, can only be retrieved and decrypted by authorized users \r\n\r\nusing our own web-application, which is hosted in our website.', '', 'KAJAL PANDURANG CHAVAN', 'BHARTI VIDYAPEETH COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING, NAVI MUMBAI', 'chavankajal2208@gmail.com', '9765582733', '101/A-3, Ashtavinayak Park', 'Rameshwadi, Badlapur(west)', 'thane', '400601', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0084/1458625030_FINAL-PAPER.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Partial Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Disagree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"