(78, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040085', 4, '2016-04-05 09:25:57', 'POLYMER MATRIX COMPOSITE OF BASALT FIBER  —A REVIEW', 'composite material', 2, 6, '', 'polymer matrix, basalt fiber, glass fiber replacement', 'In recent years increase in the use of eco-friendly, natural fibers as reinforcement for the fabrication of lightweight, low cost polymer composites can be seen globally in many applications. In particular both industrial and academic world are focusing their attention toward the development of sustainable composites, reinforced with natural fibres. Among the natural fibres basalt ones represents the more interesting properties, which is cost-effective and offers exceptional properties over glass fibers. This article presents a review on basalt fibers used as a reinforcement material for polymer matrix composites and as an alternative to the use of glass fibers.', '', 'VIGNESHWARAN K', 'ADHIYAMAAN COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING', '3vicky7@gmail.com', '9787979697', 'BAHAVATHI AMMAN KOVIL STREET,', 'GUZILIAMPARAI', 'DINDIGUL', '624703', 'TAMILNADU', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0085/1458636481_ISSTT2015TemplateWord-a.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Disagree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Agree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Agree","comment":"1)Title: Good & Appreciate \\r\\n2)Construction of manuscript: good work as review article\\r\\n3) overall ar