(79, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040086', 65, NULL, 'Prediction model on web mining', 'Web mining', 1, 11, '', 'Web Usage Mining, Markov models, Bayesian theorem, Prediction.', 'Abstract- Because of the rapid growth of the word-wide-web, the problem of predicting a user’s browsing behavior on a web-site has gained important and the need is personalize and influence a user’s browsing experience. For solving this problem Markov models and its variations have been found. Personalization, building proper websites, promotion, getting marketing information, and forecasting market trends etc, the prediction result can be used. By using Markov model the users’ browsing behaviors can be predicted at category level. Probability of present and infer users’ browsing behaviors at webpage level by applying the Bayesian theorem. The system can effectively filter the possible category of the websites by Markov models and predict websites accuracy by the Bayesian theorem . In this paper we present different techniques for prediction of users’ browsing behaviors and  intelligently selecting parts of different order Markov model. The resulting model has improved prediction accuracy and reduced state complexity. ', '', 'Pratik Bhise', 'Tulsiramji gaikwad Patil college of engineering & technology', 'Pratik.bh777@gmail.com', '9637894592', 'C/o plot no 15', 'Niwas so . manish nagar ', 'Nagpur', '440015', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0086/1458639435_final-research.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Disagree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Fully Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of w