(82, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040089', 118, '2016-04-04 17:48:16', 'M2M Communication', 'Embedded Network', 1, 12, '', 'Computer Network, Wired and Wireless Communication, PowerLink Protocol Stack', '\r\nM2M COMMUNICATION –POWERLINK TECHNOLOGY\r\n\r\nAbstract-We are describing about M2M communication.M2M stands for Machine to Machine Communication. M2M communication is nothing but machine communicates with each other. In our project, one machine acts as a server aka managing node (MN) and another acts as a client aka controller node(CN).They can send and receive data in each other. We are using 2 Raspberry pi B+ as client and server. Raspberry pi has more important features,  So we are using it.\r\nTo have the faster communication between these we use PowerLink protocol stack. It helps in transmission of time critical data. It is faster than Ethernet. These solutions are commonly referred to as “real-time industrial Ethernet” technologies. POWERLINK has become one of the most successful real-time industrial Ethernet systems. PowerLink technology is easily ported on any embedded device .It provides high speed data transfer,   ease of installation  .\r\n\r\nFuture scope- In today’s world Shop floor management is one of the most important ongoing activities performed in every Industry. On each shop floor there are few tens to thousands of machines having different parameters those impact production, machine health, performance, quality, etc. In a typical scenario, the data is manually collected in the form of reports in predetermined time. This reports are then used for analysis. There are many chances for inaccuracies into a manual data collection system. Firstly the data must be first written down, and later entered into the system sometimes by a different person than the one that recorded it in the first place. Whenever a human operator enters data, he or she has influence over exactly what information is entered and when it is entered. \r\nM2M Communication provides complete visibility of all the manufacturing work order activity. It can extend across different fields to track product activities from raw materials to finished goods. The outcome of this project is to make the shop floor intelligent. M2M Communication has a powerful reporting feature that allows you to configure and generate reports on demand, or it is also used to set up schedules to automatically deliver pre-configured reports. The M2M Communication Standard Reports are labels that can be configured to include data from a specified time period, also from specific machines, operators, part numbers or other parameters depending on machine type. \r\nIt helps to give precise and unbiased results to the top management. So it helps the top management to keep track of ongoing activities of the shop floor. The result should be a less communication gap between top management and the shop floor. This type of management helps organizations become more transparent\r\n', '', 'Pratiksha Aslekar', 'PICT,Pune', 'pratikshaaslekar@gmail.com', '9689376932', 'Katraj,Pune', 'as above', 'Pune', '411046', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0089/1458650647_PAPER.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Fully Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Fully Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Fully Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Agree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Agree","comment":"Author has Copied from the http://www.ethernet-powerlink.org/ internet source.\\r\\n\\r\\nThe Concept was clear, we can Publish.\\r\\n"}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 5, 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0089/', '3', 0, 1, 19, '2016-03-22 18:14:08', 0, '2016-04-04 22:49:24', 1, 0),
