(84, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040091', 113, NULL, 'Implementation of Adaptive DBSCAN for cluster analysis', 'Data Mining', 5, 11, '', ' Data mining, Clustering, Adaptive DBSCAN', 'The ability to monitor students’ academic performance as well as their participation in other events and managing a record for the same is a critical issue to the staff members. Encouraging the students to improve in the area were they are lacking behind is necessary. In this paper we propose a system where the staff members can update the student records in areas like academics, technical skills and participation in extracurricular activities and viewing the same whenever necessary. Further we implemented the adaptive DBSCAN for clustering the students based on their performance in various areas. Based on the resulting clusters the staffs identify the performance of each student and the students’ progress can also be monitored.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Usha G', 'KCG College of Technology', 'ushaganesan159@gmail.com', '9791132284', 'No.5 Srinivasaperumal sanathi 2nd street', 'Royapettah', 'chennai', '600014', 'Tamil Nadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0091/1458714644_adbscan-ieee.doc', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Partial Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Disagree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Partial Agree","comment":"Proposed Method which has been