(86, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040093', 130, NULL, 'GSM BASED DISTRIBUTION TRANSFORMER MONITORING AND CONTROLLING SYSTEM', 'Electrical Engineering', 1, 8, '', 'Microcontroller, Transformer, Sensors, GSM, LCD.', 'This system is about design and implementation of a mobile embedded system to monitor and record key parameters of a distribution transformer like load currents, overvoltage, oil level, winding temperature and ambient temperature. The idea of on-line monitoring system integrates a global service mobile (GSM) Modem, with a single chip microcontroller and different sensors. It is installed at the distribution transformer site and the above parameters are recorded using the analog to digital converter (ADC) of the embedded system. The obtained parameters are processed and recorded in the system memory. If any abnormality or an emergency situation occurs the system sends SMS (short message service) messages to the mobile phones containing information about the abnormality according to some predefined instructions programmed in the micro controller. This mobile system will help the transformers to operate smoothly and identify problems before any failure.', '', 'Gajare Jayshri Tukaram', 'Pune University', 'gajarejayshri@gmail.com', '9960604137', 'A/P-Gajarwadi Tal-Niphad', 'A/P-Wes Tal-Kopergaon', 'Niphad', '422303', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0093/1458721971_anu2.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Partial Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Disagree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Appl