(90, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040097', 108, NULL, 'Adaptive Policy Prediction of User Uploaded  Images on Data Sharing Sites', 'Computer Science & Engineering', 1, 4, '', 'User-uploaded images, Adaptive privacy policy prediction(A3P)', 'Social network is an emerging service which provides a reliable communication, through this communication a new attack ground for data hackers; they can easily misuses the data through these media. Facebook is most popular example of social media which enable us to communicate with lot of people. In which peoples have opportunities to meet new peoples, friends and communicate with each other. They shares images and personal data. Toward addressing this need, we propose an Adaptive Privacy Policy Prediction (A3P) system to help users compose privacy settings for their images. We will examine the role of social context, image content, and metadata as possible indicators of users’ privacy preferences. This proposes a privacy policy prediction and access restrictions along with blocking scheme for social sites using data mining techniques. We propose a two-level framework which according to the user’s available history on the site determines the best available privacy policy for the user’s images being uploaded. In this paper an Adaptive Privacy Policy Prediction is used to help user for privacy setting of their images. Our goal is to provide various privacy policy approaches to improve the privacy of images or information shared in the social media site. Over time, the generated policies will follow the evolution of users’ privacy attitude.', '', 'Miss.Yugandhara K. Nade', 'Jagadambha College Of Engineering & Technology, Yavatmal-445001', 'nade.yugandhara@gmail.com', '7405407107', 'Jagadambha College Of Engineering & Technology, Yavatmal-445001', 'Arni Rd, Near Tandoor Garden, Kinhi, Yavatmal, Maharashtra 445105', 'Yavatmal', '445105', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0097/1458753520_paper.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was goo