(113, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040107', 142, NULL, 'Addressing Cloud Data Deduplication Using Hybrid Approach', 'Computer Science and Engineering', 1, 4, '', 'Attribute Based (AB), Convergent Encryption, Deduplication', 'In cloud computing, data deduplication is one of the important data compression techniques for eliminating repeating data which are duplicate, and has been widely used in cloud storage to reduce the amount of storage space. To protect the confidentiality of those sensitive data while supporting deduplication, the convergent encryption technique has been proposed to encrypt the data before deploying . In existing approaches, only the file names are checked so that many data have been lost. In this paper, we use AB (Attribute Based) algorithm to check the files based on their attribute so it requires less time for checking all those files. After finishing this process it will check the content of the particular file, then the files having the same content re identified to be duplicated and will be eliminated, which will be more efficient.', '', 'M. Abbinayaa', 'KPR Institute of Engineering and Technology, Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India', 'abi.n.r1995@gmail.com', '7405407107', 'KPR Institute of Engineering and Technology, Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu, India', 'Kollupalayam , Arasur, Coimbatore, Tamil Nadu 641407', 'Coimbatore', '641407', 'Tamil Nadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0107/1458827619_DataDeduplication-in-cloud.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Partial Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Res