(114, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040108', 93, NULL, 'Microcontroller Based Street Light Energy Saving System', 'Electronics and telecommunications ', 5, 7, '', 'street light, LDR, PIR sensor, PIC microcontroller.', 'Nowadays, human has become too busy and unable to switch ON or OFF the street lights. The proposed system will automatically switch ON the street lights in the evening before the sunset and switch OFF in the morning when there is sufficient lights on the road.Two sensors are used-LDR is used to indicate the day or night on the street and PIR is used to detect presence of vehicle or person.The street light automation can reduce energy consumption there by it reduces cost and it is built using sensors and microcontroller. The programming language used for developing the software is C-language. ', '', 'Nagnath Savant', 'Karmayogi Engineering College Shelve Pandharpur ', 'nagnathsavant1@yahoo.com', '9922096378', 'Karmayogi Engineering College Pandharpur', 'Pandharpur', 'Pandharpur ', '413304', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0108/1458832924_ppp.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Disagree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Disagree","comment":"Title: Microcontroller Based Street Light Energy Saving System\\r\\nAuthors: Gajare S.R1 Ragade S.M2Savant N C3Patil S.P4\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n