(117, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040111', 140, NULL, 'Smartphone enabled secure access to multiple entities', 'Security', 1, 4, '', 'Credentials, Password, Security, Smartphone, Web services', 'Smartphone enabled secure access to multiple entities deals with providing privacy and security to user.It stores complex credentials of web services such as Facebook, Gmail, twitter etc. conveniently in an encrypted form.This application can authenticate user within seconds and open web services securely without typing a single word on the keyboard. ', '', 'Yoshita Ravindra Mahajan', 'Padabhushan Vasantdada Patil College Of Engineering', 'mahajanyoshita04@gmail.com', '9004373264', 'B-112, Vrindavan', 'L.B.S. Marg, Ghatkopar(west)', 'Mumbai', '400086', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0111/1458881532_SESAME.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Partial Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Disagree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Disagree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Disagree","comment":"1.NFC is not cleared in paper \\r\\n2. problem statement is weak\\r\\n3. Objective and usage  of the system is not easy to understand\\r\\n4. how connection established with smart phone "}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 6, 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0111/', '1', 0, 0, 0, '2016-03-25 10:22:12', 0, '2016-03-27 15:01:08', 1, 0),
(118, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040112', 0, NULL, 'A Study of Heat Transfer Enhancement using V Shaped Dimples on a Flat Plate with Experimentation & CFD', 'Heat Transfer Enhancement', 1, 6, '', 'Forced conve heat transfer, Nusselt Number, heat transfer enhancement, V-shaped dimples', 'Heat transfer augmentation without considerable pressure drop is one of the most important issues now a days. The different active and passive methods are used for the same. One of the passive technique is use of dimples. A depression forming recesses on a flat surface is considered as a dimple. Variation in dimple geometry results in various heat transfer and friction characteristics. Introducing the dimples on the surface not only increases the surface area available for heat transfer but also reduce the hydrodynamic resistance for the fluid flow over the surface, resulting in less pressure drop. The present work is based on experimental investigation of the forced convection heat transfer over the V-shaped dimpled surface. The experiments were performed on 150mm × 150mm × 15mm aluminium plate with V- shaped dimples with pitch 3.2D, where D = diameter of dimple. V-dimples with  δ/D = 0.2, 0.3, 0.5 are investigated, where δ= dimple depth. The experimentation was carried over a rectangular duct with aspect ratio 3:2. Heat transfer coefficient, Nusselt Number, friction factor and overall thermal performance of dimpled surface are compared with those from flat surface under same conditions. It is found that dimpled surface show 30- 45% enhancement over a flat plate. The maximum enhancement is observed in δ=0.3D in inline pattern. The dimpled surface with δ=0.5D shows minimum enhancement. Maximum frictional losses are observed in δ=0.5D dimpled surface and minimum in δ=0.2D dimpled surface. The overall thermal efficiency goes on increasing with increasing Reynolds number for all cases. The enhancement was verified using CFD analysis using ANSYSIS-15 ICEM software using k-ε turbulence model.\r\n', '', 'Amit Ranaware', 'PES’s Modern College of Engineering, Pune, India', 'ranawareamit@yahoo.co.in', '9767215821', 's.no.114/1, plot no.32,33, Chandan Appartment, Near chavan chaul,', 'Vishranwadi', 'PUNE', '411015', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0112/1458887166_FINAL-PAPER-A.G.-Ranaware.docx', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 1, 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0112/', '3', 1, 1, 0, '2016-03-25 11:56:07', 0, '2016-03-27 22:36:46', 1, 0),
(119, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040113', 91, NULL, 'DISEASES INFERENCE FROM HEALTH-RELATED INFORMATIONS VIA MAP REDUCING', 'Data analyst technique in Bigdata', 4, 11, '', 'BigData, Map Reduce, Diseases prediction, HDFS, Encrypted details,SVM', '-The intention of the work is to ensure\r\nthe correct diagnosis of any illness with the help of\r\ndecision support system. Patient’s Health records\r\n(PHR’s) are maintained in the public cloud where each\r\nand every patient is provided with an ID. All the data\r\nstored should be encrypted. Different encryption keys\r\nshould be used on different machines and the key\r\ninformation should be stored centrally behind strong\r\nfirewalls. This way even if a hacker is able to get the\r\ndata, he cannot extract meaningful information from it and\r\nmisuse it. Patient data will be stored securely in an\r\nencrypted manner.The main goals are ease of\r\nretrieval/collection of the specific information, less time\r\nconsumption, cost effective, scalable, Fault tolerant and\r\nincrease in security.', '', 'S.Sandhya', 'Dhanalakshmi College of Engineering', 'sandhyaselvamani248@gmail.com', '9841272123', '57/118 P.E.koil north mada street', 'Ayanavaram', 'Chennai', '600023', 'Tamilnadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0113/1458891021_ljournal.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Partial Agree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disag