(121, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040115', 142, NULL, 'm-commerce using nfc tags', 'computer technology', 1, 12, '', 'NFC, Mobile Commerce, Virtual shopping, NFC tags, NFC App', 'This paper presents a novel method to create an Android based M-commerce application using NFC. It would require Mobile Devices which support NFC technology. NFC stands for Near Field Communication technology which is a short-range, high frequency, low bandwidth radio technology that allows transferring data within few centimeters. In traditional shopping, the customer needs to physically pick up the items to be purchased and carry cash or credit/debit cards with them to make payments. The application mentioned here would read the NFC tag(s) of the product(s) & add it to the shopping cart in our application. It would also provide methods to change the quantity of product/s purchased and edit the cart. Along with this the customer would be informed about the on-going offers in the store. Payment could be made through cash or online using existing payment methods. The paper would also throw light on NFC based payments.', '', 'Sneha Nair', 'Thakur Polytechnic', 'snehanair0020@gmail.com', '8108334460', '401,Meera Palace,Mira Village road,Behind Amar Palace Hotel', 'western express highway, Dist- Thane', 'Mumbai', '401104', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0115/1458891608_m-commerce-using-NFC-tags-manuscript.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Partial Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Disagree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematica