(126, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040120', 65, NULL, 'Multicloud Resource Allocation and Deployment with Migration of Virtual Resources for Green Computing', 'Cloud Computing', 1, 11, '', 'Virtualization, Green computing, Dynamic Resource Allocation, Virtual Machines, cache mechanism', 'Virtualization is a technology, it is a way to achieve optimum resource utilization for the hardware to achieve cloud computing. In this paper, we provide a detailed description of the dynamic resource allocation technique in the cloud and the problem of Dynamic Migration of Virtual Machines (DM-VM) is investigated.  We implemented a new BGM-BLA (Binary Graph Matching –based Bucket code Learning Algorithm) algorithm for DM-VM problem, this dynamic migration of VM provides a method to distribute physical resource more reasonably without suspending the services. Therefore the energy consumption, load balancing and operation cost is reduced. We also implemented a cache mechanism in order to avoid replicating request to the server using this technique can achieve the Green Computing.', '', 'Keerthiga R', 'Dhanalakshmi College of Engineering, Chennai', 'keerthithara07@gmail.com', '7405407101', 'Dhanalakshmi College of Engineering, Chennai', 'Dhanalakshmi College of Engineering, Chennai', 'Chennai', '123456', 'AP', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0120/1458899529_original-paper.doc', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Fully Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Disagree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Disagree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Disagree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all he