(136, 4, 0, 'GRDJEV01I040123', 110, NULL, 'COMMUNICATION OVER INTERNET AND GSM USING SMART DOORBELL ', 'Internet Of Things', 1, 4, '', 'GSM, Internet of things, Raspberry pi, smart living', '\r\n \r\nThis paper presents the concept of enabling communication between a visitor at the door of a house and its owner in a situation when the owner is not available at home. 	There are no smart and convenient ways, at present, for the the owner to be notified about the presence of a visitor at his/her door .The world of ‘Internet of Things’ with Raspberry pi at its core allows a fascinating scope to ensure the same.Embedding a standard household doorbell into IOT and GSM network, the system provides a set of features which ensure that no visitor is left unattended or goes unnoticed by the owner of the house  in cases when he or she is at work, out of station or just taking a nap on a lazy afternoon. As smarter living is at the core of this project, the system also recognizes and distinguishes the user’s family and  friends and therefore  does   not bother the user with any unrequired notifications. \r\n', '', 'Prashant Singh', 'S.I.E.S Graduate School of technology,Navi mumbai,nerul', 'prashantsingh.leo27@gmail.com', '9768907696', '13,jagannath smruti,shastri nagar,old dombivli road', 'dombivli west.', 'dombivli', '421202', 'maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I04/0123/1458904226_GRD-PAPER.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application