(191, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050001', 61, NULL, 'Fatigue Analysis of Bearing', 'Mechanical Engineering', 1, 6, '', 'rolling bearings, fatigue, finite element method', 'The development of the technology of rolling bearings has as one of its objectives constitute a set of mechanical components that combine mechanical strength and stiffness, designed to support the loads, speeds and life specified for a particular application. This work aims to discuss the application of the finite element method in the analysis of fatigue failure in rolling bearings, evaluating the influence of some construction and operational parameters in the stress distribution, such as geometry of contact surfaces, applied load, rotation, and properties of materials in contact. Specifically, we investigated the relationship between the stress caused by cyclic loading in fatigue life of these bearings. The analysis of the life of rolling bearings was performed using the commercial software, based on the finite element method in a virtual environment. Expected that the results obtained in this study will be useful in developing methods for predicting fatigue failure in rolling bearings.', '', 'Ms.Shelke A. A.', 'JCOE Kuran Pune 410511', 'shelkeamruta.007@gmail.com', '8796266404', 'JCOE Kuran Pune 410511', 'Junnar Narayangaon SH 52, Pimpalgaon T Narayangaon, Maharashtra 410502', 'Pune', '410502', 'Maharashtra', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0001/1458970082_Fatigue-analysis-of-Bearing.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Resu