(212, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050002', 142, NULL, 'VIDEO COMPRESSION USING ENCODING TECHNIQUE', 'COMPRESSION USING ENCODING', 6, 11, '', 'COMPRESION', 'The process of reducing the size of a data file is known as data compression. Compression can be of two types lossy or lossless. In lossless compression  bits are reduced by identifying and eliminating redundancy. None information is lost in lossless compression and Lossy compression reduces bits by identifying unnecessary or redundant information and removing it. Data compression or bit-rate reduction involves encoding information using fewer bits than the original representation. In the context of data transmission, it is called source coding encoding done at the source of the data before it is stored or transmitted through network.\r\nCompression is of two types lossy or lossless. Lossless compression is preferred more than lossy for archival purposes and often for medical imaging, technical drawings, video clips, clip art, or comics and cartoon films. Lossy compression method is required especially when used at low bit rates, Lossy methods are especially suitable for natural images such as original photographs in applications where minor loss of accuracy is acceptable to achieve a substantial  Reduction in bit rate. The lossy compression which cannot identify differences may be called visually lossless. Compression is used because it helps reduce \r\n\r\nresource usage, like data storage space or transmission capacity.\r\nCompressed data must be decompressed to use, this extra process thrusts some computational or other costs through decompression method. Data compression is subject to a space–time complexity trade-off. For example, a compression scheme for video may requires expensive hardware for the video to be decompressed fast enough to be viewed as it is being decompressed, and the option to decompress the video in full it may be inconvenient or require additional storage. The design of data compression strategy involves trade-offs among various factors, including the degree of compression, the amount of distortion introduced ,when using lossy data compression and the computational resources required to compress and decompress the data.\r\n', '', 'LAXMI YADAV', 'THEEM COLLEGE OF ENGINEERING,BOISAR', 'ylaxmi565@gmail.com', '7208644028', 'VINOBA BHAVE NAGAR,C-BLOCK,6/5,PIPE ROAD.', 'KURLA (WEST)', 'MUMBAI', '400070', 'MAHARASHTRA', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0002/1458983888_publish-Video-Compression.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Partial Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Disagree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Partial Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Disagree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Disagree","comment":"Paper is rejected because\\r\\n1. It is not research/survey paper because only 2 bibliography papers are not enough. \\r\\n2. Paper can not be written like as Theory and Encoding Theory and technical content is not enough to explain heading.\\r\\n3. Result is not displayed as title of paper.\\r\\n4. Paper format is not followed by author"}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 6, 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0002/', '3', 0, 0, 0, '2016-03-26 14:48:08', 0, '2016-03-31 10:24:22', 1, 0),
