(233, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050004', 50, NULL, 'Knee joint modeling using laser scanner technique.', 'Reverse engineering', 1, 6, '', '3D Cad Model, Laser Scanner', 'Knee joint is the most important joint in the human body. 3D CAD modelling is the most important part for analysis Reverse engineering is one of the process by which 3D CAD model can be easily generated. Different techniques available for generating CAD models. The paper describes the methodology applied in the development of an anatomically detailed three-dimensional knee model from 3D laser scanner machine. 3D laser scanner machine is used for generating CAD model which requires 3D solid model as a input. It is made of box type and then solid model id kept on platform provided in box. Laser rays are applied on the periphery of the model and return time of the laser is calculated by which the model is generated on monitor screen.', '', 'Prof. Vijay Parmar', 'Vadodara Institute of Engineering, Kotambi', 'vijay.parmar20@gmail.com', '9228822821', 'B-203, Shivam Enclave', 'Ajwa Road', 'Vadodara', '390019', 'Gujrat', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0004/1459013180_GRD-paper-new.doc', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Agree","comment":"1. The paper alignment is not properly done\\r\\n2. The compar