(236, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050006', 58, NULL, 'Street light energy conservation system using PIR sensor', 'Electronics and telecommunications ', 5, 7, '', 'Street light , Low power consumption ,LDR,PIR sensor,Microcontroller', 'This paper proposes energy efficient automatic street lighting system based on low cost microcontroller. The main objective is to design energy efficient based controller for controlling the Light Emitting Diode (LED) based street lamp via appropriate lighting levels control. This system consists of a microcontroller, light sensor, PIR sensor and a set of the LED module.  The controlling and managing of the system is based on the density of traffic and five different level of street light brightness has been used for lighting up street proportional to the density of traffic. The system was programmed to automatically turn off during the night. Several numbers of tests have been conducted to test and validate the proposed prototype in the different environment. As conclusion, around 77%-85% reduction in power consumption can be achieved through this proposed automatic street lighting system for energy efficiency system design.', '', 'Nagnath Savant', 'Karmayogi Engineering College Shelve Pandharpur', 'nagnathsavant1@yahoo.com', '9922096378', 'Karmayogi Engineering College Shelve Pandharpur ', 'Pandharpur ', 'Solapur', '413304', 'Maharashtra ', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0006/1459074829_ias-1.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Partial Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Partial Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Disagree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was 