(238, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050008', 54, NULL, 'AVOID COLLISION AND BROADCAST DELAY IN MULTIHOP COGNITIVE RADIO AD-HOC NETWORK USING SELECTIVE BROADCASTING', 'WIRELESS SENSOR NETWORK', 1, 7, '', 'BASED ON COGNITIVE RADIO ADHOC NETWORK', 'Cognitive networks enable efficient sharing of the radio spectrum. Control signals are used to setup a communication with the broadcast to the neighbors in their respective channels of operation. But in cognitive network the number of channels is potentially large, broadcasting control information over all channels will cause a large delay in setting up the communication. Thus, exchanging control information is a critical issue in cognitive radio networks. This paper deals with selective broadcasting in multi-hop cognitive radio networks in which, control information is transmitted over pre-selected set of channels. We introduce the concept of neighbor graphs and minimal neighbor graphs, to derive the essential set of channels for transmission. It is shown through simulations that selective broadcasting reduces the delay in broadcast the information and it assures the successful transmission of information to all its neighbors. It is also demonstrated that selective broadcasting reduces redundancy in control information and hence reduces network traffic.', '', 'S.VICHITHRA', 'IFET college of engineering', 'vichithrapdy@gmail.com', '9578263025', '35,karunagarapillai street', 'DR nagar', 'pondycherry', 'pondy', 'pondycherry', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0008/1459140797_vvv1.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Partial Agree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Resu