(248, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050018', 0, NULL, 'DESIGN AND COST ANALYSIS OF RURAL AND URBAN TOILET', 'CIVIL ENGINEERING + RURAL AND URBAN TOILETS IN SURA CITY', 4, 10, '', 'Rural,Urban,Toilet,ECOSAN.Design,Costing,Survey', 'Providing sanitation is India remains a huge challenge.  This study explores the difficult that occur due to sanitation in rural and urban India through the approach of conducting a field survey in the areas. The survey results are analyses and solution of the problem is provided. The solution involves providing an ecological sanitation (ECOSAN) TOILET. AutoCAD drawing of the designed toilet are provided for better understanding. The response of public on the design toilet suggested was studied with help of another survey to know the preference of the people. Along with design the cost of conventional toilet posed a great challenge for successful sanitation in rural areas. This study aims to reduce the cost of toilet construction by removing pit system as well as changing the superstructure material. The cost comparison of various toilet and those with different superstructure material is presented. The initial cost of EcoSan toilets, which is about Rs. 10520, is slightly higher than ordinary pit latrines or offset double pit latrines, EcoSan toilets provide benefits in terms of fertiliser. A financial analysis of cost and benefits of EcoSan toilets indicates that the pay-back period for an EcoSan toilet is 6 years, Benefit To Cost Ratio of 1.17( At I=10%) and the Financial Internal Rate of Return (FIRR) is 14.527  percent. However social acceptability of our designed toilet remains uncertain. In a Comparison matrix, which includes four different latrine designs, the designed ECOSAN receive the highest scores (21 out of 27) for a given set of design and evaluation criteria. Potential areas for cost reductions and design improvements are identified', '', 'SHYAM DOSHI', 'Civil Engineering Department, Chhotubhai Gopalbhai Patel Institute of Technology', 'shyam.doshi@utu.ac.in', '7575030400', 'h/203, manthan, muktanand nagar, opp. sardar bridge', 'adajan surat', 'surat', '395009', 'gujarat', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0018/1459698943_paper.docx', '', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 1, 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0018/', '3', 1, 1, 0, '2016-04-03 21:25:44', 0, '2016-04-03 21:25:44', 0, 0),
(249, 5, 0, 'GRDJEV01I050019', 131, '2016-04-05 11:14:35', 'TRAFFIC CONTROL SYSTEM FOR CONGESTION CONTROL AND STOLEN VEHICLE DETECTION', 'Embedded System', 2, 14, '', 'RFID', ' This project presents a smart traffic control system to avoid traffic congestion and to trap stolen vehicles . Each  individual vehicle is equipped with special radio frequency identification (RFID) tag (placed at a strategic location), which makes it impossible to remove or destroy. We use RFID reader, and  PIC16F877A  system-on-chip to read the RFID tags attached to the vehicle. It counts number of vehicles that passes on a particular path during a specified duration. It also determines the network congestion, and hence the green light duration for that path. ', '', 'Priyanka.N', 'Sri Eshwar College of Engineering', 'priyankanatarajan34@gmail.com', '9003654051', '2/235 Gandhinagar,', 'Kinathukadavu', 'Coimbatore', '642109', 'Tamilnadu', 'India', 'GRDJE/V01/I05/0019/1459699258_project-journal.docx', '{"Title construction of manuscript was good":"Agree","Introduction covers each part of work done area Introduction covers all required thorough":"Agree","Knowledge to understand the topic":"Partial Agree","Material method was given with company detail":"Partial Agree","All materials were covered which was used in that work":"Partial Agree","Method was describe in details":"Disagree","Method was describe with quantity of materials used in that work":"Partial Agree","Result was discussed thoroughly to understand the effect of work":"Disagree","Result was discussed with mathematical model Application":"Disagree","Acknowledgement was described all help which was received during the work":"Disagree","I do not have any objection if this work was published in this journal":"Disagree","comment":"this paper is not in our journal standards. page alignments are not correct .results are not discussed in this paper. need some more corrections in data ,and page formatting.  "}', 0, '', '', 0, 0, '', NULL, 3, 